-- Boltz1 (MIT License) --
Boltz: Democratizing Biomolecular Interaction Modeling.
Copyright (c) 2024 Jeremy Wohlwend, Gabriele Corso, Saro Passaro, et al.
Source: https://github.com/jwohlwend/boltz

ProteoR1's structure-generation backbone (proteor1/generate/) is derived from
Boltz1. The structure prediction core, diffusion sampler, confidence module,
and training-time MSA processing logic in proteor1/generate/ are
re-implementations of components originally released under the MIT License.

-- Protenix (Apache License 2.0) --
Protenix: structure prediction model.
Copyright (c) 2024 ByteDance Ltd. and/or its affiliates.
Source: https://github.com/bytedance/Protenix

ProteoR1's structure-encoder dependency (used by proteor1/understand/)
relies on the Protenix encoder, distributed under Apache 2.0. The Protenix
encoder is consumed via the `protenix_dev` package (git submodule:
https://github.com/smiles724/protenix_dev), not vendored into this repository.

-- Thinking Bio Lab (Apache License 2.0) --
This project's public release packaging, the joint understand+generate
training pipeline (internal, not shipped), and the prepare-cdr CLI are
authored by Thinking Bio Lab and released under Apache 2.0. Only the
inference-side code is distributed in this open-source release.

